Rinse the @brown basmati rice{1} thoroughly under cold running water. Boil a large #pot of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Add the rice and cook on high heat for ~{25%minutes} until cooked through. Drain and cover with a #lid and keep to one side.

Peel and finely dice the @garlic{1%clove}. Peel the @ginger{1/2} using the edge of a #spoon and finely dice. Finely slice the @spring onions{2} into discs, separating the whites from the green parts.

Mix the @soy sauce{2} with the @honey{1}, half the garlic, the ginger and the whites from the spring onions. Cut the @flank steak{1} into wafer thin strips and marinate in the teriyaki mix for as long as you can.

Cut the @pak choi{2} in half lengthways and then slice thinly widthways. Discard the root when you've cut down as far as you can.

Heat a #pan with @oil{1%tbsp} over a high heat. Add the steak and fry for a few mins, remove from the #pan.

> Fry off the steak in batches to make sure you keep the pan nice and hot.

> Leave the remaining marinade in the bowl, so you can brown off the steak first.

Once the steak is removed from the pan, add the rest of the marinade to the pan and allow to thicken slightly. Then add the steak back in.

In a separate #pan heat @oil{1%tbsp} over a medium heat. Add the remaining garlic and cook until it just starts to change colour. Add the bok choy and @salt{1/4%tsp} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the rice and mix then cook until it's heated through.

Serve the rice topped with the teriyaki beef and sprinkle over the green parts of the spring onions and of course the @black sesame seeds{1}!